  "articleSummary": "The article presents a personal, enthusiastic analysis of programming languages, focusing on the author’s evolving admiration for JavaScript (particularly ES6) and Rust. The core thesis argues that ES6’s improved syntax, tooling (e.g., BabelJS), and productivity gains have transformed JavaScript into the author’s “One True Love,” while Rust is praised for its safety, performance, and modern design despite immature web frameworks. Key technologies discussed include ES6 features (classes, destructuring), BabelJS, and Rust’s memory management. The tone is informal and passionate, using metaphors like “radioactive spider-bite” and “KoolAid” to frame language adoption as an addictive but rewarding shift. Intended for developers evaluating language ecosystems, the piece blends technical examples with subjective enthusiasm.",
